# Product Requirements Document (PRD)

## VideoAI – Smart Video Organizer with AI Summarization & Interactive Q&A

**Date:** July 23, 2025

---

### 1 · Introduction

#### 1.1 Purpose of the Document

This PRD defines the updated scope, features, and technical requirements for **VideoAI**, enabling the development team to deliver the next product increments with clarity and shared understanding.

#### 1.2 Product Overview  (updated)

**VideoAI** is a smart video‑management application that lets users upload personal videos and unlock AI‑powered insights. Each video is automatically transcribed, summarized, and indexed so learners, creators, and knowledge‑seekers can **instantly surface key moments** and ask questions without re‑watching lengthy footage. Users can search their library by topic or keyword, attach personal notes, and retrieve exactly the clip—or idea—they need.

---

### 2 · Objectives & Goals

1. Provide a **mobile‑first**, frictionless platform for organising personal video libraries.
2. Enable AI‑driven **summaries, topic extraction, and interactive Q&A** for every uploaded video.
3. Deliver **fast, intuitive search** across videos, notes, and AI‑generated metadata.
4. Support **>50 videos per user** while keeping costs predictable.
5. Maintain a secure, privacy‑respecting architecture with minimal user setup.

---

### 3 · Features & Functionality

#### 3.1 Video Upload & Storage

- **Primary (Phase 2 – *****done*****):** upload from device gallery or camera, real‑time progress, metadata capture.
- **Deferred (Phase 6):** URL‑based ingest (YouTube, TikTok)—subject to TOS & bandwidth review.

#### 3.2 User Notes & Key Points

- Markdown‑style notes linked to timestamps.

#### 3.3 AI Processing Pipeline

- **Transcription** via Whisper.
- **Summarisation** (GPT‑4 / Claude) → “TL;DR” + topic tags.
- **Embeddings** stored in `pgvector` for semantic search.

#### 3.4 Interactive Q&A (RAG)

- Embed user query → similarity search → context‑aware answer with clickable timestamps.

#### 3.5 Search & Discovery

- Hybrid keyword + vector search across titles, notes, summaries.
- Filters: date, duration, custom tags.

#### 3.6 Swipe‑Up Insight Panel

- Swipe on any video to reveal summary, notes, and chat.

---

### 4 · Technical Requirements  (unchanged core stack)

- **Frontend:** Expo (React Native) PWA.
- **Auth:** Supabase Auth.
- **Storage:** Supabase Storage (Pro tier) – 100 GB included; reevaluate S3 hybrid > 1 TB.
- **Database:** Supabase Postgres + pgvector.
- **Edge Functions:** Supabase (Deno) for signed URLs & AI hooks.
- **Background Jobs:** Supabase Queues / Trigger.dev.
- **LLM APIs:** OpenAI, Anthropic, Gemini.
- **Vector Search:** pgvector.
- **CDN:** Fastly (built‑in).

---

### 5 · User Experience Highlights

- **Home Feed:** grid of thumbnails.
- **Upload Tab:** choose from gallery or record.
- **Insight Panel:** swipe‑up for summary + chat.
- **Search Bar:** global, instant results.

---

### 6 · Constraints & Assumptions (updated)

- Initial cohort <10 users; Supabase **Pro** tier covers 100 GB → extra GB at \$0.021.
- AI cost monitoring in place; fallback models if token usage spikes.
- URL ingest postponed until legal & cost implications resolved.

---

### 7 · Timeline & Milestones (re‑aligned)

| Phase                                | Status         | Target       | Key Deliverables                                           |
| ------------------------------------ | -------------- | ------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------- |
| **1. Foundation**                    | ✅ Complete     | –            | Auth, Storage, DB, CI/CD                                   |
| **2. Upload & Gallery**              | ✅ Complete     | –            | Device upload, metadata, feed                              |
| **3. AI Processing**                 | 🚧 In progress | Aug 2025     | Audio extraction, transcription, summarisation, embeddings |
| **4. Interactive Q&A & Swipe‑Up UI** | Planned        | Sep 2025     | Chat panel, source‑linked answers                          |
| **5. Search & Discovery**            | Planned        | Oct 2025     | Hybrid search, filters                                     |
| **6. URL Ingest (optional)**         | Deferred       | TBD          | Server‑side fetch, TOS compliance                          |
| **7. Polish + Analytics**            | Planned        | Oct/Nov 2025 | Push notifications, error tracking                         |

---

### 9 · Appendices  (unchanged)

#### 9.1 Technology Stack Summary

- **Frontend:** Expo
- **Auth:** Supabase Auth
- **Storage:** Supabase Storage
- **Database:** Supabase Postgres with pgvector
- **Functions:** Supabase Edge Functions
- **Queue:** Supabase Queues
- **LLM APIs:** OpenAI, Anthropic, Gemini
- **Vector Search:** pgvector
- **CDN:** Supabase built‑in (Fastly)

---

> **Open question:** should we introduce AWS S3 + Glacier for cold storage once >1 TB is reached? Current plan is to stay on Supabase until that threshold.

